  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Architect/Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Report to senior architectural designer</li>\n  <li>Collaboration in space planning assignments, conceptual design, schematic design, design development, design documentation and construction site supervision for design implementation.</li>\n  <li>Plan, schedule and run design activities to meet the project programme.</li>\n  <li>Preparation of communicative presentations (in pptx or other media)</li>\n  <li>Preparation of coherent sets of design-focused tender drawings</li>\n  <li>Coordination with consultants, vendors, contractors, fabricators, regulatory agencies and other collaborators to meet overall project objectives.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all designs meet with local regulatory compliance requirements.</li>\n  <li>Review of shop drawings submittals and finish samples</li>\n  <li>Conducting site observations to monitor construction progress and to ensure that planning and design intent are fully realised at site.</li>\n  <li>Contribution to refinement of office design processes</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Singaporean or Singapore PR only</li>\n  <li>3-5 years of experience in the design industry.</li>\n  <li>Bachelor or Master Degree in Architecture or Interior Design.</li>\n  <li>Experience in Healthcare, Laboratory, Nursing homes, Special needs facilities and workplace preferred but not necessary. However, willingness to learn is a must.</li>\n  <li>Excel in 3D modelling, visualization, and graphic software; Revit skillset is strongly preferred. (Others include acad, Sketch-up, Enscape, adobe and Microsoft suites).</li>\n  <li>Effective verbal and written communication skills</li>\n  <li>Motivated with the ability to work independently and as a team.</li>\n  <li>Available for business travel if necessary.</li>\n  <li>Have a keen desire to produce good and aesthetic designs. A good eye for good aesthetics is a plus.</li>\n  <li>Familiar with local codes and building practices is preferred, but not necessary.</li>\n</ul>",
